<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-07T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-07T14:36:00-05:00" n="1157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1157">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4824.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-07T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>There appears to be a movement of concentration among the revolutionary
                            elements in disturbed southern States. I have to-day received a notice
                            sent to me as dean of the diplomatic corps, to be communicated to my
                            colleagues, of the intention of the revolutionary forces to attack
                            Mexico City at an early date. Notice is well drawn and sent for the
                            purpose of reassuring the people of Mexico City of <pb facs="0955" n="839" xml:id="pg_839"/> the intention of the revolutionists to
                            maintain order and protect all noncombatants. I shall take no action
                            relative thereto.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>